reliable color output, compact design, and the ability to print double-sided (either auto- or manual duplex). Note if models offer auto duplexing. •\tHighlight which models include smart/AI features such as app support, remote printing, ink monitoring, and error self-diagnosis (HP Smart, Canon Print, Epson iPrint, Alexa/Google integration, etc.). 3.\tLive Amazon Product Links & Availability: •\tOnly include models that have verified, working U.S. Amazon.com links as of today. For each model, display the current lowest Amazon price and provide a clickable (Markdown-format) hyperlink to the product page. Table Requirements: •\tPresent the results in a clean, readable Markdown table. Include these columns: Model, Amazon Link, Price, Color/Compact, Duplex Type, Ink Efficiency (estimated monthly cost & type), Smart/AI Features, Special Benefits, and Replacement Ink Cost. •\tUse clear, concise bullet points or short sentences in each cell for easy comparison. •\tAdd a brief 2–3 sentence summary at the top of the table recommending best picks for light users who want to minimize ink waste and total cost. Extra Instructions: •\tExclude laser-only or mono printers unless they are notably cost-efficient for home users. •\tOnly include Canon printers like PIXMA TS6420a or MegaTank G3270 if Amazon links are valid. •\tDouble-check that all Amazon links are current and lead to the U.S. product page (not an error or unrelated result). •\t(Optional) Briefly compare ink tank vs. cartridge vs. laser models for total cost of ownership in light-use scenarios. I'll conduct comprehensive research on compact home color printers available on Amazon US, focusing on cost efficiency for light users (50 pages/month). Let me gather current pricing, specifications, and verified product links. Using Tool | Product Search HP Smart Tank color printer compact duplex View Using Tool | Product Search Epson EcoTank color printer compact duplex View Using Tool | Product Search Canon MegaTank G3270 G4270